20	 * dependencies injected via constructor.  Spring Data repository calls each open
21	 * their own transaction, so this class has no `@Transactional` annotation.
22	 *
23	 * <h3>Lifecycle</h3>
24	 * <ol>
25	 *   <li>Mark job RUNNING in DB.</li>
26	 *   <li>Load pending queue from checkpoint (or start with {@code baseUrl}).</li>
27	 *   <li>Reconstruct visited set from {@code crawl_pages} rows already in DB.</li>
28	 *   <li>Crawl loop: throttle → fetch → incremental check → extract → discover links.</li>
29	 *   <li>Save checkpoint every {@link #checkpointInterval} pages.</li>
30	 *   <li>On pause/cancel signal: save checkpoint and return early.</li>
31	 *   <li>Mark final status (COMPLETED / PAUSED / CANCELLED / FAILED).</li>
32	 * </ol>
